ue\\n    # Question: Of these norm violations (violate_care, violate_fairness, violate_loyalty, violate_authority, violate_sanctity, violate_liberty), which one does it most violate?\\n    answer = violate_fairness(I)\\n    # Solve the problem\\n    # By conditional law (p -> q): covering_up_truth -> deception -> dishonest_behavior -> harm_reputation -> cheating_and_deception. The bridge to the specific violation will be determined by the solver.\\n    # The answer is true.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\"\"\"\\nI tore down the birthday decorations for tomorrow.\\nQuestion: Of these norm violations (violate_care, violate_fairness, violate_loyalty, violate_authority, violate_sanctity, violate_liberty), which one does it most violate?\\n\"\"\"\\n# explanation: there is an emotional harm made to a human. the act of tearing down the decorations is an act of causing emotional harm. birthday decorations are typically set up by someone who cares for the birthday person.\\n# solution in Python:\\ndef solution():\\n    # I tore down the birthday decorations for tomorrow.\\n    action(I, tearing_down_decorations) = True\\n    # the act of tearing down the decorations is an act of causing emotional harm.\\n    implies(tearing_down_decorations, emotional_harm) = True\\n    # there is an emotional harm made to a human.\\n    implies(emotional_harm, harm_to_human) = True\\n    # birthday decorations are typically set up by someone who cares for the birthday person.\\n    implies(birthday_decorations, set_up_by_caring_person) = True\\n    # Question: Of these norm violations (violate_care, violate_fairness, violate_loyalty, violate_authority, violate_sanctity, violate_liberty), which one does it most violate?\\n    answer = violate_care(I)\\n    # Solve the problem\\n    # By conditional law (p -> q): tearing_down_decorations -> emotional_harm -> harm_to_human. The bridge to the specific violation will be determined by the solver.\\n    # The answer is true.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\"\"\"\\nI was bored and